Context:
The George Brown College Student Association offers health and dental insurance to all full-time students. The student health and dental plan fee is mandatory and is included in tuition fees for full-time students. Students have the option to opt out of the coverage. There are four different coverage plans to choose from: Balanced Plan (automatically covered for domestic post-secondary and ESL students, as well as international students registered in a post-secondary program), and three other Enhanced Plan options. The plan choice is valid for the entire academic year and cannot be changed until the following September.
